# macOS Native Patterns

## NSPanel (Notch Window)

- Style: `.borderless, .nonactivatingPanel, .utilityWindow, .hudWindow`
- Level: `.mainMenu + 3` (above everything except dock)
- `canBecomeKey: false`, `canBecomeMain: false` — never steals focus
- `hidesOnDeactivate: false` — stays visible when app loses focus
- `collectionBehavior: [.canJoinAllSpaces, .stationary, .fullScreenAuxiliary, .ignoresCycle]`

## NSStatusItem (Menu Bar)

- Create: `NSStatusBar.system.statusItem(withLength:)`
- Remove: `NSStatusBar.system.removeStatusItem()`
- Always cancel tracking before removing
- `isTemplate = true` for images (auto light/dark adaptation)

## Multi-Display

- `NSScreen.screens` to list displays
- Display UUID via `CGDisplayCreateUUIDFromDisplayID`
- One NotchWindowController per screen
- Zombie pattern: 8s grace period for temporarily disconnected displays

## Notch Detection

- `screen.auxiliaryTopLeftArea` for hardware notch presence
- `screen.safeAreaInsets.top` for notch height
- Fallback to menu bar height

## App Lifecycle

- `NSApp.setActivationPolicy(.accessory)` — no dock icon
- `SMAppService` for login item (macOS 13+)
- Must install in /Applications for login item to work

## Haptics

- `NSHapticFeedbackManager.defaultPerformer.perform(.alignment, performanceTime: .default)`
- Only on closed notch hover
- User-configurable (can be disabled)

## System Wake Recovery

- `NSWorkspace.didWakeNotification` for wake detection
- Multi-attempt recovery: [300, 800, 1500, 3000]ms delays
- Reconcile all controllers each attempt
